{"lemma":"حُجْراتُ","slug":"حُجْراتُ","root":"ح.ج.ر","root_slug":"ح-ج-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ج-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حُجْرَة","root":"حجر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7151","n7162","n7163","n7164"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8F%D8%AC%D9%92%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"room, compartment, cell, chamber"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħud͡ʒ.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7151","headword_ar":"حجّرهُ","root":"Hjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 5. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hj~r Hawola A^aroDihi","text_ar":"حجّر حَوْلَ اَرْضِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made a bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an enclosure, around his land"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A. [Perhaps from what next follows; or the reverse may be the case.]) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hj~r Eayona AlaEiyri","text_ar":"حجّر عَيْنَ الَعِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHojiyrN","text_ar":"تَحْجِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He burned a mark round the eye of the camel with a circular cauterizing instrument:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hj~r Eayona Ald~aAb~api","text_ar":"حجّر عَيْنَ الدَّابَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolahaA","text_ar":"حَوْلَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hawola EayonihaA","text_ar":"حَوْلَ عَيْنِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as is said in the A,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he burned a mark round the eye of the beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~ara AlbaEiyru","text_ar":"حَجَّرَ البَعِيرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camel had a mark burned round each of his eyes with a circular cauterizing instrument."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [Perhaps this may be a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~ira AlbaEiyru","text_ar":"حُجِّرَ البَعِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haj~ara AlbaEiyra","text_ar":"حَجَّرَ البَعِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he burned a mark round each of the eyes of the camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: but see what follows.]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hj~r Alqamaru","text_ar":"حجّر القَمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n. as above, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The moon became surrounded by a thin line, which did not become thick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and (S [in the K “ or ”])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became surrounded by a halo in the clouds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S K,)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n7162","headword_ar":"حَجْرَةٌ","root":"Hjr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A severe year, that confines men to their tents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"houses, so that they slaughter their generous camels to eat them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nbt","text_ar":"نبت"},{"kind":"text","text":", on a verse of Zuheyr.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A side; an adjacent tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajorapN","text_ar":"حَجْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (EM p. 281:) pl. of the former ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajorN","text_ar":"حَجْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or rather this is a coll. gen. n., of which the former is the n. un.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajaraAtN","text_ar":"حَجَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAjiru","text_ar":"حَوَاجِرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the last is mentioned by ISd as being thought by him to be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajorapN","text_ar":"حَجْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense above explained, contr. to analogy. (TA.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajorapN qawomK","text_ar":"حَجْرَةٌ قَوْمٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter adjacent to the abode of a people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajorataA AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"حَجْرَتَا الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two sides of the road."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajorataA EasokarK","text_ar":"حَجْرَتَا عَسْكَرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two sides of an army;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its right and left wings."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEada HajorapF","text_ar":"قَعَدَ حَجْرَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sat aside."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAra HajorapF","text_ar":"سَارَ حَجْرَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He journeyed aside, by himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHojarFA","text_ar":"مَحْجَرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also said to signify the same, in the following ex.:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taroEaY maHojarFA","text_ar":"تَرْعَى مَحْجَرًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wataboruku wasaTFA","text_ar":"وَتَبْرُكُ وَسَطًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pastures aside, and lies down in the middle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarobiDu HajorapF wayarotaEiY wasaTFA","text_ar":"يَرْبِضُ حَجْرَةً وَيَرْتَعِى وَسَطًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lies down aside, and pastures in the middle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroEaY wasaTFA wayarobiDu HajorapF","text_ar":"يَرْعَى وَسَطًا وَيَرْبِضُ حَجْرَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one pastures in the middle, and lies down aside:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) applied to a man who is in the midst of a people when they are in prosperity, and when they become in an evil state leaves them, and lies down apart: the prov. is ascribed to Gheylán Ibn-Mudar. (IB.) Imra-el--Keys says, [addressing Khálid, in whose neighbourhood he had alighted and sojourned, and who had demanded of him some horses and riding-camels to pursue and overtake a party that had carried off some camels belonging to him (Imra-el-Keys), on Khálid's having gone away, and returned without anything,]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"fadaEo Eanoka nahobFA SiyHa HajaraAtihi\n                      \n                     \n                        wal`kino HadiyvFA maA Hadyvu Alr~awaAHili"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then let thou alone spoil by the sides of which a shouting was raised: but"},{"kind":"text","text":"relate to me"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a story. What is the story of the riding-camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"?]: hence the prove.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHukomu lil~hi","text_ar":"الحُكْمُ لِلّهِ"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wadaEo Eanoka nahobFA SiyHa fiY HajaraAtihi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dominion belongeth to God: then let thou alone"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; said with reference to him who has lost part of his property and after that lost what is of greater value. (TA.) [And hence the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadi A@nota$arato Hajoratuhu","text_ar":"قَدِ ا@نْتَشَرَتْ حَجْرَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His property has become large, or ample."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajorN","text_ar":"حَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n7163","headword_ar":"حُجْرَةٌ","root":"Hjr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An enclosure"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaZiyrapN","text_ar":"حَظِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-  [And hence,] The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hujorap","text_ar":"حُجْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a house; (S;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a chamber"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in an absolute sense, and so in the present day]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotN","text_ar":"بَيْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an upper chamber;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurofapN","text_ar":"غُرْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HujarN","text_ar":"حُجَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HujuraAtN","text_ar":"حُجُرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HujaraAtN","text_ar":"حُجَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HujoraAtN","text_ar":"حُجْرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Z, Msb, K.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajorapN","text_ar":"حَجْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n7164","headword_ar":"حِجْرَةٌ","root":"Hjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HijorN","text_ar":"حِجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}